Stamford Bridge is located in Fulham, London. It is the home ground of Chelsea F.C.. The stadium is located within the Moore Park Estate also known as Walham Green and is often referred to as simply The Bridge. The capacity is 41,631, making it the eighth largest ground in the 2017 18 Premier League season. The club has plans to expand the capacity to 60,000 by the 2021 2022 season. When expansion starts, Chelsea intend to play at Wembley Stadium until they return in 2023
